MEBOL)|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 8. || 29 May 1996 || [[Miami Orange Bowl]], [[Miami]], United States || {{fb|SCO}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center> || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 9. || 7 July 1996 || rowspan=4 | [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Mel\u00e9ndez]], [[Barranquilla]], Colombia || {{fb|URU}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || <center>3\u20131</center> || rowspan=5 | [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 10. || rowspan=3 | 1 September 1996 || rowspan=3 | {{fb|CHI}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || rowspan=3 | <center>4\u20131</center>\n|-\n| 11. || <center>'''2'''\u20130</center>\n|-\n| 12. || <center>'''4'''\u20130</center>\n|-\n| 13. || 9 October 1996 || [[Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Atahualpa]], [[Quito]], Ecuador || {{fb|ECU}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center>\n|-\n| 14. || 8 February 1997 || [[Estadio Hern\u00e1n Ram\u00edrez Villegas]], [[Pereira, Colombia|Pereira]], Colombia || {{fb|SVK}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || <center>1\u20130</center> || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 15. || 20 August 1997 || [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Mel\u00e9ndez]], [[Barranquilla]], Colombia || {{fb|BOL}} || <center>'''3'''\u20130</center> || <center>3\u20130</center> || [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 16. || rowspan=\"2\"|9 February 1999 || rowspan=\"2\"|[[Miami Orange Bowl]], [[Miami]], United States || rowspan=\"2\"|{{fb|GER}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || rowspan=\"2\"|<center>3\u20133</center> || rowspan=4 | [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 17. || <center>'''2'''\u20132</center>\n|-\n| 18. || rowspan=\"2\"|17 June 1999 || rowspan=\"2\"|[[Estadio Palogrande]], [[Manizales]], Colombia || rowspan=\"2\"|{{fb|PER}} || <center>'''1'''\u20133</center> || rowspan=\"2\"|<center>3\u20133</center>\n|-\n| 19. || <center>'''2'''\u20133</center>\n|-\n| 20. || 19 February 2000 || [[Miami Orange Bowl]], [[Miami]], United States || {{fb|USA}} || <center>'''1'''\u20131</center> || <center>2\u20132</center> || [[2000 Gold Cup]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Atl\u00e9tico Nacional'''\n*[[Categor\u00eda Primera A]]: 1991\n*[[Copa Interamericana]]: 1990\n\n'''Parma'''\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[1998\u201399 Coppa Italia|1998\u201399]]\n*[[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|European Cup Winners' Cup]]: [[1992\u201393 European Cup Winners' Cup|1992\u201393]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup|European Super Cup]]: [[1993 European Super Cup|1993]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]: [[1995 UEFA Cup Final|1994\u201395]], [[1999 UEFA Cup Final|1998\u201399]]\n\n'''Palmeiras'''\n*[[Rio-S\u00e3o Paulo Tournament]]: 2000\n*[[Brazilian Champions Cup]]: 2000\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|id=12577}}\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/asprilla-intlg.html International statistics] at [[rsssf]]\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{Webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050920222207/http://www.squarefootball.net:80/article/inbrief.asp?iid=840 |date=20 September 2005 |title=Whatever happened to Faustino Asprilla}}\n*[http://fourfourtwo.com/interviews/one-on-one/127/article.aspx Interview] with FourFourTwo\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Colombia squads\n| bg=#FCD116\n| fg=#003893\n| bordercolor=#CE1126\n|list1=\n{{Colombia football squad 1992 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Colombia squad 1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Colombia squad 1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Colombia squad 1995 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Colombia squad 1997 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Colombia squad 1998 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Colombia squad 2000 CONCACAF Gold Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Asprilla, Faustino}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Valle del Cauca Department]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Colombian footballers]]\n[[Category:Colombian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Colombia international fo